8 An Act relating to education; specifying
apportionment of certain appropriated funds;
9 providing for the budgeting of funds in certain
categories and amounts; requiring development of
10 certain performance measures; requiring transfers of
certain funds; limiting authority to reduce certain
11 apportionments; requiring certain funds to be
expended for certain purposes; stating purposes for
12 allocated funds; requiring certain transfer of funds;
stating legislative intent regarding expenditures for
13 direct costs; prohibiting the State Department of
Education from contracting for certain administrative
14 costs in certain program; providing for duties and
compensation of employees of the State Department of
15 Education; requiring the reduction or withholding of
State Aid funds for certain purposes; authorizing the
16 State Board of Education to request transfer of
certain funds; authorizing the request of early
17 allocations for certain funds; requiring proportional
reductions of allocations under certain conditions;
18 authorizing exemption from budgetary limits for
unanticipated federal funds; providing procedures;
19 requiring approval of exemption request under certain
conditions; requiring budgeting of certain funds in
20 certain years; requiring certain budgeting
procedures; prohibiting certain budgeting procedures;
21 appropriating certain funds in certain amount for
certain purpose; directing utilization of certain
22 amounts for certain purposes; providing for
noncodification; providing an effective date; and
23 declaring an emergency.
