9 SECTION 16. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
10 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
11 The Superintendent of Public Instruction may request through the
12 Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise Services the
13 early transfer by the Oklahoma Tax Commission of tax collections to
14 the Education Reform Revolving Fund for the purpose of early
15 allocation to the State Board of Education's disbursing funds to
16 alleviate cash-flow problems.
17 SECTION 17. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
18 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
19 If funds appropriated in Sections 1 through 22 of Enrolled
20 Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session of the 60th Oklahoma
21 Legislature are not sufficient to fully fund the provisions of this
22 act, each school district that qualifies for funds, excluding
23 Financial Support of Public Schools, pursuant to the provisions of
24 this act shall take a proportionate reduction.
