1 SECTION 18. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
2 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
3 A. The State Superintendent of Public Instruction may request,
4 in the manner provided in this section, that receipt and expenditure
5 of unanticipated federal funds awarded after July 1, 2026, be exempt
6 from expenditure limitations and from budgetary limitations.
7 1. The Superintendent shall make a request for exemption to the
8 Office of Management and Enterprise Services in writing and file a
9 revised budget work program.
10 2. The Superintendent shall also file copies of the request for
11 exemption and budget work program revisions with the chair of the
12 Appropriations Committee of the Oklahoma State Senate and the chair
13 of the Appropriations and Budget Committee of the Oklahoma House of
14 Representatives. The chair of the Appropriations Committee of the
15 Oklahoma State Senate and/or the chair of the Appropriations and
16 Budget Committee of the Oklahoma House of Representatives shall
17 notify the Office of Management and Enterprise Services of any
18 noncompliance of the request with legislative intent within twelve
19 (12) calendar days of receipt of the exemption request.
20 B. The Office of Management and Enterprise Services shall
21 approve the request for exemption unless both the chair and vice
22 chair of the Legislative Oversight Committee on State Budget
23 Performance provide written notification to the Office of Management
24 and Enterprise Services within twelve (12) calendar days of the
ENGR. H. B. NO. 4030 Page 13

1 Comm ittee's receipt of the exemption request that the exemption
2 subverts the intention and objectives of the Legislature in
3 establishing the original limit. The Office of Management and
4 Enterprise Services shall give written notice of approval or
5 disapproval of each exemption to the agency, the Governor, the chair
6 of the Appropriations Committee of the Oklahoma State Senate, and
7 the chair of the Appropriations and Budget Committee of the Oklahoma
8 House of Representatives within eighteen (18) calendar days of
9 receiving the request.
10 SECTION 19. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
11 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
